Author: WAKEFIELD
Vol / Page: 127
Edition:
Quote: Similar stations to those formed in the Wairarapa have lately been established by squatters from Wellington, at Kaikoura, a fine district of pastoral country ...
Notes:

Date: 0/0/1848
Source: Letters & Journals
Author: STEPHENS
Vol / Page: 463
Edition:
Quote: These people [who left England penniless and are now wealthy] are all squatters upon the soil - they have never to this day paid a farthing of rent for the land they occupy ... This is detrimental to the legitimate farmer and owner of the land - making it impossible to compete with parties who have never paid anything.
Notes:

